"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989485","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-10-25","<p>The Department of Health and Social Care has provided £16 billion to local authorities over five years for public health services, including for alcohol and drug treatment, and there are currently no plans to increase this funding further.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-10-25T14:04:18.597Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989485/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989485/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989485/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-17","Buprenorphine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether he plans to increase local authority funding for substance misuse services as a result of changes in the cost of prescribing buprenorphine.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","180690"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989486","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2018-10-25","<p>The Secretary of State has not met the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care to discuss the prescribing of buprenorphine. Funding to local authorities for public health is provided by the Department of Health and Social Care.</p>","Richmond (Yorks)","Rishi Sunak",,"2018-10-25T14:04:43.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989486/answer","Biography information for Rishi Sunak","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989486/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989486/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2018-10-17","Buprenorphine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care on the financial effect on substance misuse services of the changes in the cost of prescribing buprenorphine.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","180691"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989487","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-25","<p>The Secretary of State for Health and Social Care regularly meets with Cabinet colleagues to discuss a range of topics. The Government has committed £16 billion in funding to local authorities over the current five-year spending review period to tackle public health issues, which includes alcohol and drug treatment services, and there are no plans to increase funding further at this time.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","180693","2018-10-25T11:50:19.103Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989487/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989487/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989487/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-17","Buprenorphine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what discussions he has had with the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government on the financial effect of the increase in the cost of prescribing buprenorphine on the provision of substance misuse services.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","180692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989488","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-10-26","<p>The Government is committed to ending the use of unabated coal for electricity generation by 2025. Government measures and support for low carbon technologies mean that coal has gone from generating 39% of the UK’s electricity in 2012 to 7% in 2017[i]. Coal’s share of electricity generation was 1.6% for 2018 Q2. Gas’ share of electricity generation was 42% for the same period[ii].</p><p> </p><p>The Department considers and analyses a range of future price scenarios and the effect on anticipated generation from coal and gas; a number of these scenarios are published as part of the BEIS Energy and Emissions Projections[iii]. Changes in gas prices are one of a number of factors that can affect the amount of coal and gas generation on the system at any particular time. Higher gas prices may incentivise some switching from gas to coal due to impacts on gas-fired power plants relative profitability in the short term. While there may be a small increase in the share of coal generation this winter, we do not expect these recent fluctuations to significantly affect the trajectory to the end of unabated coal by 2025.</p><p> </p><p>[i] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-chapter-5-digest-of-united-kingdom-energy-statistics-dukes" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-chapter-5-digest-of-united-kingdom-energy-statistics-dukes</a></p><p>[ii] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-section-5-energy-trends" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/electricity-section-5-energy-trends</a></p><p>[iii] <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/energy-and-emissions-projections" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/energy-and-emissions-projections</a></p>","Devizes","Claire Perry",,"2018-10-26T10:46:40.03Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989488/answer","Biography information for Claire Perry","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989488/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989488/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-10-17","Electricity Generation","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, whether it is the Government's policy to move away from using coal to generate electricity in the UK; and what assessment his Department has made of the effect of higher gas prices on the level of electricity generation from (a) coal and (b) gas.","false","Biography information for Drew Hendry","Inverness, Nairn, Badenoch and Strathspey","Drew Hendry","180812"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989489","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-10-25","<p>The Secretary of State for Health and Social Care regularly meets with Cabinet colleagues to discuss a range of topics. The Government has committed £16 billion in funding to local authorities over the current five-year spending review period to tackle public health issues, which includes alcohol and drug treatment services, and there are no plans to increase funding further at this time.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine","180692","2018-10-25T11:50:19.167Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989489/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989489/answer",,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/989489/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-10-17","Buprenorphine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, whether his Department has allocated additional funding to substance misuse services as a result of the increase in the cost of prescribing buprenorphine.","false","Biography information for Dr Dan Poulter","Central Suffolk and North Ipswich","Dr Dan Poulter","180693"
